      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "In my years of experience, recursion in languages like Java is dangerous because it is very easy to eat all of your system&#39;s resources by accident. You could do it, but I wouldn&#39;t. But maybe an alternative would be to use a loop to build a nested stream, then run the stream. You can&#39;t really have an infinite loop in streams from my understanding."
