    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Since <a href=\"/questions/tagged/java-16\" class=\"post-tag\" title=\"show questions tagged &#39;java-16&#39;\" rel=\"tag\">java-16</a>, you can use <code>Stream#mapMulti</code></p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>List&lt;Object&gt; result = listOfLists.stream()\n                                 .mapMulti((List&lt;Object&gt; list, Consumer&lt;Object&gt; consumer) -&gt; {\n                                     list.forEach(consumer::accept);\n                                 })\n                                 .collect(Collectors.toList());\n</code></pre>\n<p>If you need an immutable <code>List</code> you can even use <code>toList()</code> as terminal operation</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>List&lt;Object&gt; result = listOfLists.stream()\n                                 .mapMulti((List&lt;Object&gt; list, Consumer&lt;Object&gt; consumer) -&gt; {\n                                     list.forEach(consumer::accept);\n                                 })\n                                 .toList();\n</code></pre>\n"
